com.gemalto.mfs.mwsdk.provisioning.model

Enum ProvisioningServiceCodeType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ProvisioningServiceCodeType>
      • com.gemalto.mfs.mwsdk.provisioning.model.ProvisioningServiceCodeType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ProvisioningServiceCodeType>

    public enum ProvisioningServiceCodeType
extends Enum<ProvisioningServiceCodeType>
    During the enrollment or card activation phase, the end user is able to enter the following codes:
    1. The activation code
    2. The mobile PIN
    This will be the enumeration of the type of verification required. If the EnrollingServiceListener.onCodeRequired(com.gemalto.mfs.mwsdk.utils.chcodeverifier.CHCodeVerifier) is called, this will determine what type of input is expected from the end user.

      • ACTIVATION_CODE

        public static final ProvisioningServiceCodeType ACTIVATION_CODE
        This implies that the user is expected to enter the activation code.

      • MOBILE_PIN

        public static final ProvisioningServiceCodeType MOBILE_PIN
        This implies that the user is expected to enter the mobile pin. The user is expected to enter a pin having 4-12 digits long. Failing to comply with this length will result in the SDK returning an error code ProvisioningServiceErrorCodes.CARD_ACTIVATION_MOBILE_PIN_INVALID_LENGTH . Should this error code be returned, the SDK will expect the activation code to be entered again, before allowing the end-user to re-enter the mobile pin.
